href="jonmsterling.xml"
addr="jonmsterling"
title="Jon Sterling">Jon Sterling</fr:link></fr:author></fr:authors></fr:frontmatter><fr:mainmatter>
 <fr:p>By assumption, we have an <fr:link
type="local"
href="jms-00ME.xml"
addr="jms-00ME"
title="Enumerable set">enumeration</fr:link> <fr:tex
display="inline"><![CDATA[e_I\colon  \mathbb {N}\twoheadrightarrow  I]]></fr:tex>; as each <fr:tex
display="inline"><![CDATA[A_i]]></fr:tex> is <fr:link
type="local"
href="jms-00ME.xml"
addr="jms-00ME"
title="Enumerable set">enumerable</fr:link>, we may use the <fr:link
type="local"
href="jms-00MM.xml"
addr="jms-00MM"
title="The axiom of choice">axiom of choice</fr:link> to assign to each <fr:tex
display="inline"><![CDATA[i\in  I]]></fr:tex> a specific <fr:tex
display="inline"><![CDATA[e_i\colon  \mathbb {N}\twoheadrightarrow  A_i]]></fr:tex>.</fr:p>
 <fr:p>Let <fr:tex
display="inline"><![CDATA[h\colon \mathbb {N}\twoheadrightarrow \mathbb {N}\times \mathbb {N}]]></fr:tex> be any <fr:link
type="local"
href="jms-00ME.xml"
addr="jms-00ME"
title="Enumerable set">enumeration</fr:link> of <fr:tex
display="inline"><![CDATA[\mathbb {N}\times \mathbb {N}]]></fr:tex>. Define <fr:tex
display="inline"><![CDATA[k\colon \mathbb {N}\times \mathbb {N}\to  A]]></fr:tex> as follows:</fr:p>
 <fr:tex
display="block"><![CDATA[   k{\mathopen {}\left (m,n\right )\mathclose {}} = e_{e_I{\mathopen {}\left (m\right )\mathclose {}}}{\mathopen {}\left (n\right )\mathclose {}}  ]]></fr:tex>

 <fr:p>The function <fr:tex
display="inline"><![CDATA[k\colon \mathbb {N}\times \mathbb {N}\to  A]]></fr:tex> is <fr:link
type="local"
href="jms-00M8.xml"
addr="jms-00M8"
title="Surjection">surjective</fr:link>: fixing <fr:tex
display="inline"><![CDATA[a\in  A]]></fr:tex>, we must find <fr:tex
display="inline"><![CDATA[{\mathopen {}\left (m,n\right )\mathclose {}}]]></fr:tex> such that <fr:tex
display="inline"><![CDATA[k{\mathopen {}\left (m,n\right )\mathclose {}}=a]]></fr:tex>. Let <fr:tex
display="inline"><![CDATA[i=\pi _A{\mathopen {}\left (a\right )\mathclose {}}]]></fr:tex>; because <fr:tex
display="inline"><![CDATA[e_I]]></fr:tex> is <fr:link
type="local"
href="jms-00M8.xml"
addr="jms-00M8"
title="Surjection">surjective</fr:link>, we may find <fr:tex
display="inline"><![CDATA[m\in  \mathbb {N}]]></fr:tex> such that <fr:tex
display="inline"><![CDATA[e_I{\mathopen {}\left (m\right )\mathclose {}}=\pi _A{\mathopen {}\left (a\right )\mathclose {}}]]></fr:tex>, and because <fr:tex
display="inline"><![CDATA[e_{\pi _A{\mathopen {}\left (a\right )\mathclose {}}}]]></fr:tex> is <fr:link
type="local"
href="jms-00M8.xml"
addr="jms-00M8"
title="Surjection">surjective</fr:link>, we may find <fr:tex
display="inline"><![CDATA[n\in  \mathbb {N}]]></fr:tex> such that <html:span
xmlns:html="http://www.w3.org/1999/xhtml"
style="white-space: nowrap"><fr:tex
display="inline"><![CDATA[e_{\pi _A{\mathopen {}\left (a\right )\mathclose {}}}{\mathopen {}\left (n\right )\mathclose {}} = a]]></fr:tex>.</html:span> Therefore, we have <fr:tex
display="inline"><![CDATA[k{\mathopen {}\left (m,n\right )\mathclose {}} = e_{e_I{\mathopen {}\left (m\right )\mathclose {}}}{\mathopen {}\left (n\right )\mathclose {}} = e_{\pi _A{\mathopen {}\left (a\right )\mathclose {}}}{\mathopen {}\left (n\right )\mathclose {}}=a]]></fr:tex>.</fr:p>
</fr:mainmatter><fr:backmatter /></fr:tree>
 
