type="user">jms-00NF</fr:addr><fr:route>jms-00NF.xml</fr:route><fr:title
text="Cantor’s theorem">Cantor’s theorem</fr:title><fr:taxon>Theorem</fr:taxon><fr:date><fr:year>2024</fr:year><fr:month>1</fr:month><fr:day>31</fr:day></fr:date><fr:authors><fr:author><fr:link
type="local"
href="jonmsterling.xml"
addr="jonmsterling"
title="Jon Sterling">Jon Sterling</fr:link></fr:author><fr:contributor><fr:link
type="local"
href="marcelofiore.xml"
addr="marcelofiore"
title="Marcelo Fiore">Marcelo Fiore</fr:link></fr:contributor></fr:authors></fr:frontmatter><fr:mainmatter><fr:p>Given any set <fr:tex
display="inline"><![CDATA[A]]></fr:tex>, there can be no <fr:link
type="local"
href="jms-00M8.xml"
addr="jms-00M8"
title="Surjection">surjection</fr:link> from <fr:tex
display="inline"><![CDATA[A]]></fr:tex> to <fr:tex
display="inline"><![CDATA[\mathcal {P}{\mathopen {}\left (A\right )\mathclose {}}]]></fr:tex>.</fr:p>
 
   
   <fr:tree
toc="false"
numbered="true"
show-heading="true"
show-metadata="false"
expanded="true"
root="false"
xmlns:fr="http://www.jonmsterling.com/jms-005P.xml"><fr:frontmatter><fr:anchor>2195</fr:anchor><fr:addr
type="machine">#371</fr:addr><fr:route>unstable-371.xml</fr:route><fr:taxon>Proof</fr:taxon><fr:date><fr:year>2024</fr:year><fr:month>1</fr:month><fr:day>31</fr:day></fr:date><fr:authors><fr:author><fr:link
type="local"
href="jonmsterling.xml"
addr="jonmsterling"
title="Jon Sterling">Jon Sterling</fr:link></fr:author></fr:authors></fr:frontmatter><fr:mainmatter>
 <fr:p>Assume that we <fr:em>do</fr:em> have a <fr:link
type="local"
href="jms-00M8.xml"
addr="jms-00M8"
title="Surjection">surjection</fr:link> <fr:tex
display="inline"><![CDATA[e\colon  A\twoheadrightarrow \mathcal {P}{\mathopen {}\left (A\right )\mathclose {}}]]></fr:tex>. Consider the subset <fr:tex
display="inline"><![CDATA[U\in \mathcal {P}{\mathopen {}\left (A\right )\mathclose {}}]]></fr:tex> defined below:</fr:p>
 <fr:tex
display="block"><![CDATA[   U = {\mathopen {}\left \{x\in  A\,\middle \vert \,x\not \in  e{\mathopen {}\left (x\right )\mathclose {}}\right \}\mathclose {}}  ]]></fr:tex>

 <fr:p>Because <fr:tex
display="inline"><![CDATA[e\colon  A\twoheadrightarrow \mathcal {P}{\mathopen {}\left (A\right )\mathclose {}}]]></fr:tex> is <fr:link
type="local"
href="jms-00M8.xml"
addr="jms-00M8"
title="Surjection">surjective</fr:link>, we may find some <fr:tex
display="inline"><![CDATA[a\in  A]]></fr:tex> such that <fr:tex
display="inline"><![CDATA[e{\mathopen {}\left (a\right )\mathclose {}}=U]]></fr:tex>.</fr:p>

 <fr:p>Thus for each <fr:tex
display="inline"><![CDATA[x\in  A]]></fr:tex>, we have
 <fr:tex
display="inline"><![CDATA[    x\in  e{\mathopen {}\left (a\right )\mathclose {}}    \Longleftrightarrow     x\in  U    \Longleftrightarrow     x\not \in  e{\mathopen {}\left (x\right )\mathclose {}}  ]]></fr:tex>. Setting <fr:tex
display="inline"><![CDATA[x:= a]]></fr:tex>, we have <fr:tex
display="inline"><![CDATA[a\in  e{\mathopen {}\left (a\right )\mathclose {}} \Longleftrightarrow  a\not \in  e{\mathopen {}\left (a\right )\mathclose {}}]]></fr:tex>, a contradiction.</fr:p>
</fr:mainmatter><fr:backmatter /></fr:tree>
 
</fr:mainmatter><fr:backmatter /></fr:tree><fr:tree
toc="true"
numbered="true"
show-heading="true"
show-metadata="false"
expanded="true"
root="false"
xmlns:fr="http://www.jonmsterling.com/jms-005P.xml"><fr:frontmatter><fr:anchor>2197</fr:anchor><fr:addr
type="user">jms-00NG</fr:addr><fr:route>jms-00NG.xml</fr:route><fr:title
text="Fixed point">Fixed point</fr:title><fr:taxon>Definition</fr:taxon><fr:date><fr:year>2024</fr:year><fr:month>1</fr:month><fr:day>31</fr:day></fr:date><fr:authors><fr:author><fr:link
type="local"
href="jonmsterling.xml"
addr="jonmsterling"
title="Jon Sterling">Jon Sterling</fr:link></fr:author><fr:contributor><fr:link
type="local"
href="marcelofiore.xml"
addr="marcelofiore"
title="Marcelo Fiore">Marcelo Fiore</fr:link></fr:contributor></fr:authors></fr:frontmatter><fr:mainmatter><fr:p>A <fr:em><fr:strong>fixed point</fr:strong></fr:em> of a function <fr:tex
display="inline"><![CDATA[f\colon  X\to  X]]></fr:tex> is an element <fr:tex
display="inline"><![CDATA[x\in  X]]></fr:tex> such that <fr:tex
display="inline"><![CDATA[f{\mathopen {}\left (x\right )\mathclose {}}=x]]></fr:tex>.</fr:p></fr:mainmatter><fr:backmatter /></fr:tree><fr:tree
toc="true"
numbered="true"
show-heading="true"
show-metadata="false"
expanded="true"
root="false"
xmlns:fr="http://www.jonmsterling.com/jms-005P.xml"><fr:frontmatter><fr:anchor>2200</fr:anchor><fr:addr
type="user">jms-00NH</fr:addr><fr:route>jms-00NH.xml</fr:route><fr:title
text="Lawvere’s fixed point theorem">Lawvere’s fixed point theorem</fr:title><fr:taxon>Theorem</fr:taxon><fr:date><fr:year>2024</fr:year><fr:month>1</fr:month><fr:day>31</fr:day></fr:date><fr:authors><fr:author><fr:link
type="local"
href="jonmsterling.xml"
addr="jonmsterling"
title="Jon Sterling">Jon Sterling</fr:link></fr:author><fr:contributor><fr:link
type="local"
href="marcelofiore.xml"
addr="marcelofiore"
title="Marcelo Fiore">Marcelo Fiore</fr:link></fr:contributor></fr:authors></fr:frontmatter><fr:mainmatter><fr:p>Given sets <fr:tex
display="inline"><![CDATA[A]]></fr:tex> and <fr:tex
display="inline"><![CDATA[X]]></fr:tex>, if there exists a <fr:link
type="local"
href="jms-00M8.xml"
addr="jms-00M8"
title="Surjection">surjection</fr:link> <fr:tex
display="inline"><![CDATA[A\twoheadrightarrow {\mathopen {}\left (A\to  X\right )\mathclose {}}]]></fr:tex> then every function <fr:tex
display="inline"><![CDATA[X\to  X]]></fr:tex> has a <fr:link
type="local"
href="jms-00NG.xml"
addr="jms-00NG"
title="Fixed point">fixed point</fr:link>; and hence <fr:tex
display="inline"><![CDATA[X]]></fr:tex> is a singleton.</fr:p>
 
   
   <fr:tree
toc="false"
numbered="true"
show-heading="true"
show-metadata="false"
expanded="true"
root="false"
xmlns:fr="http://www.jonmsterling.com/jms-005P.xml"><fr:frontmatter><fr:anchor>2203</fr:anchor><fr:addr
type="machine">#370</fr:addr><fr:route>unstable-370.xml</fr:route><fr:taxon>Proof</fr:taxon><fr:date><fr:year>2024</fr:year><fr:month>1</fr:month><fr:day>31</fr:day></fr:date><fr:authors><fr:author><fr:link
type="local"
href="jonmsterling.xml"
addr="jonmsterling"
title="Jon Sterling">Jon Sterling</fr:link></fr:author></fr:authors></fr:frontmatter><fr:mainmatter>
 <fr:p>Let <fr:tex
display="inline"><![CDATA[e\colon  A\twoheadrightarrow {\mathopen {}\left (A\to  X\right )\mathclose {}}]]></fr:tex> be a <fr:link
type="local"
href="jms-00M8.xml"
addr="jms-00M8"
title="Surjection">surjection</fr:link>.
 Let <fr:tex
display="inline"><![CDATA[f\colon  X\to  X]]></fr:tex> be a function of which are trying to find a <fr:link
type="local"
href="jms-00NG.xml"
addr="jms-00NG"
title="Fixed point">fixed point</fr:link>. Let <fr:tex
display="inline"><![CDATA[h\colon  A\to  X]]></fr:tex> be the following function:</fr:p>

 <fr:tex
display="block"><![CDATA[   h{\mathopen {}\left (a\right )\mathclose {}} = f{\mathopen {}\left (e{\mathopen {}\left (a\right )\mathclose {}}{\mathopen {}\left (a\right )\mathclose {}}\right )\mathclose {}}  ]]></fr:tex>

 <fr:p>Because <fr:tex
display="inline"><![CDATA[e\colon  A\twoheadrightarrow {\mathopen {}\left (A\to  X\right )\mathclose {}}]]></fr:tex> is a <fr:link
type="local"
href="jms-00M8.xml"
addr="jms-00M8"
title="Surjection">surjection</fr:link>, we may find <fr:tex
display="inline"><![CDATA[a_h\in  A]]></fr:tex> such that <fr:tex
display="inline"><![CDATA[e{\mathopen {}\left (a_h\right )\mathclose {}} = h]]></fr:tex>. Therefore, we have <fr:tex
display="inline"><![CDATA[e{\mathopen {}\left (a_h\right )\mathclose {}}{\mathopen {}\left (a_h\right )\mathclose {}} = f{\mathopen {}\left (e{\mathopen {}\left (a_h\right )\mathclose {}}{\mathopen {}\left (a_h\right )\mathclose {}}\right )\mathclose {}}]]></fr:tex> and so <fr:tex
display="inline"><![CDATA[e{\mathopen {}\left (a_h\right )\mathclose {}}{\mathopen {}\left (a_h\right )\mathclose {}}]]></fr:tex> is a <fr:link
type="local"
href="jms-00NG.xml"
addr="jms-00NG"
title="Fixed point">fixed point</fr:link> of <fr:tex
display="inline"><![CDATA[f]]></fr:tex>.</fr:p>

 <fr:p>Finally, we conclude that <fr:tex
display="inline"><![CDATA[X]]></fr:tex> is a singleton: first of all <fr:tex
display="inline"><![CDATA[X]]></fr:tex> has at least one element (the fixed point of the identity function). Now, let <fr:tex
display="inline"><![CDATA[x_0\not = x_1\in  X]]></fr:tex> be two unequal elements of <fr:tex
display="inline"><![CDATA[X]]></fr:tex> and let <fr:tex
display="inline"><![CDATA[f\colon  X\to  X]]></fr:tex> be the function that sends <fr:tex
display="inline"><![CDATA[x_0]]></fr:tex> to <fr:tex
display="inline"><![CDATA[x_1]]></fr:tex> and everything else to <fr:tex
display="inline"><![CDATA[x_0]]></fr:tex>. By assumption, we have a fixed point <fr:tex
display="inline"><![CDATA[p\in  X]]></fr:tex> of <fr:tex
display="inline"><![CDATA[f]]></fr:tex>. We now proceed by cases:</fr:p>
 <fr:ol><fr:li>If <fr:tex
display="inline"><![CDATA[p=x_0]]></fr:tex>, then we have <fr:tex
display="inline"><![CDATA[f{\mathopen {}\left (p\right )\mathclose {}}=x_1]]></fr:tex> and <fr:tex
display="inline"><![CDATA[f{\mathopen {}\left (p\right )\mathclose {}}=p]]></fr:tex> and thus <fr:tex
display="inline"><![CDATA[x_0=x_1]]></fr:tex>, a contradiction.</fr:li>
  <fr:li>If <fr:tex
display="inline"><![CDATA[p\not = x_0]]></fr:tex>, then we have <fr:tex
display="inline"><![CDATA[f{\mathopen {}\left (p\right )\mathclose {}}=x_0]]></fr:tex> and <fr:tex
display="inline"><![CDATA[f{\mathopen {}\left (p\right )\mathclose {}}=p]]></fr:tex>, also a contradiction.</fr:li></fr:ol>
</fr:mainmatter><fr:backmatter /></fr:tree>
 
</fr:mainmatter><fr:backmatter /></fr:tree><fr:tree
