type="local"
href="jms-00I7.xml"
addr="jms-00I7"
title="Relation">relation</fr:link> on a set <fr:tex
display="inline"><![CDATA[A]]></fr:tex>.</fr:p><fr:ol><fr:li>An element <fr:tex
display="inline"><![CDATA[m\in  S\subseteq  A]]></fr:tex> is a <fr:em><fr:strong><html:span
xmlns:html="http://www.w3.org/1999/xhtml"
style="white-space: nowrap"><fr:tex
display="inline"><![CDATA[\prec ]]></fr:tex>-minimal</html:span></fr:strong></fr:em> (henceforth, “minimal”) element of <fr:tex
display="inline"><![CDATA[S]]></fr:tex> when <fr:tex
display="inline"><![CDATA[\lnot {\mathopen {}\left (\exists  x\in  S\mathpunct {.} x\prec  m\right )\mathclose {}}]]></fr:tex>.</fr:li>
 <fr:li>The binary <fr:link
type="local"
href="jms-00I7.xml"
addr="jms-00I7"
title="Relation">relation</fr:link> <fr:tex
display="inline"><![CDATA[\prec ]]></fr:tex> on <fr:tex
display="inline"><![CDATA[A]]></fr:tex> is called <fr:em><fr:strong>well-founded</fr:strong></fr:em> whenever each non-empty subset of <fr:tex
display="inline"><![CDATA[A]]></fr:tex> has a minimal element.</fr:li></fr:ol></fr:mainmatter><fr:backmatter /></fr:tree><fr:tree
